Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.08,0:00:04.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.92,0:00:07.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I bring you marvelous illusions that \Nmake this town sparkle at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.22,0:00:12.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I hope you enjoy the miracle of seeing \Nthe true face of a hated villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.47,0:00:18.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.81,0:00:22.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief has to be \Nhiding somewhere around here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.21,0:00:29.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,{\a6}This is finally the night I'm gonna \Nslap iron bracelets on those wrists!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.26,0:00:30.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This isn't good...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.05,0:00:35.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The forecast called for rain, but I didn't \Nknow it'd be too heavy for my hang glider!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.26,0:00:39.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It sounds like you're in a spot \Nof trouble, Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:43.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,U-Um... And who might you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.55,0:00:44.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.27,0:00:47.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My name is Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:52.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.96,0:02:27.26,Signs - Thief Title,,0,0,0,,Dark Knight
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.56,0:02:27.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nightmare?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.38,0:02:31.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're saying he helped Kid escape,\N Superintendent Chaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.26,0:02:32.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.81,0:02:37.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The Second Investigation Division \Njust got a mail about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.58,0:02:41.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It said, "This time, I'm meeting \NKid the Phantom Thief as a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:45.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,On next Friday night, the 13th, at 8:00p.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.56,0:02:51.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,the two of us will show you a \Nnightmare at the Shuho Art Museum."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.53,0:02:54.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Who is this "Nightmare"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.58,0:02:57.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A weird guy who wears a mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.84,0:03:01.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But he partners up with thieves \Nfrom all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.01,0:03:07.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's a mysterious mastermind who takes half \Nof the loot as his reward for coming up with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.49,0:03:09.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,the perfect methods and escape route.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.22,0:03:11.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Why would Kid team up with him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.11,0:03:17.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The good news is that any thief who \Ncooperates with him is invariably caught by
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.30,0:03:19.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,the local police before dawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.98,0:03:24.35,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and some have even been \Nshot trying to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.35,0:03:27.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Still clutching their half of the spoils...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.52,0:03:33.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So there's a rumor going \Naround among thieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.18,0:03:39.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Anyone who works with Nightmare and \Nsafely makes it through the night
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.60,0:03:46.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,will be able to shake off any nightmares of \Nthis world and attain endless good fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.01,0:03:52.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Kid the Phantom Thief is \Nblinded by the promise of good fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:55.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This way, you'll finally be \Nset free from Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.26,0:03:58.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I mean, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.12,0:04:03.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Thieves who are singled out by Nightmare \Neither end up caught or dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.64,0:04:06.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Although, as a representative \Nof Japanese law enforcement,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.40,0:04:10.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I hope to catch both of them alive \Nby any means possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.30,0:04:12.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Japanese...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.50,0:04:17.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nightmare is an international criminal \Nwho wreaks havoc all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.53,0:04:21.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Naturally, agents will be \Ncoming here with a Red Notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.09,0:04:23.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Red Notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.20,0:04:28.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,An international arrest warrant seeking \Ncustody of a fugitive criminal,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.42,0:04:30.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,demanding we turn him over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.70,0:04:31.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You didn't know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.80,0:04:34.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then don't tell me these agents \Nthat are coming over...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.80,0:04:38.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The international police organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.33,0:04:40.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Interpol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.06,0:04:45.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,136 officers in front! 103 officers in back!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.63,0:04:49.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,185 officers in the main building! \N47 officers on the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.57,0:04:52.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Six helicopters! Everyone is in place!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.23,0:04:55.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All right! Stand by in position\N until it's time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.69,0:04:57.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Keep your eyes open!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.74,0:04:59.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.49,0:05:01.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Glad you could make it, Interpol!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.66,0:05:04.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm Nakamori, the guy who's \Ngot this place locked down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.25,0:05:06.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Uh... Kaito-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.54,0:05:09.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Right. You called me here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.46,0:05:14.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. I wanted you take a look \Nat my security system here later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.62,0:05:16.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Like Kid, you're good with tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.14,0:05:20.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Check it out with an illusionist's eyes,\N then give me your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.40,0:05:21.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.51,0:05:22.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,See you later, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:24.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.33,0:05:29.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, that suits me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.76,0:05:34.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Since he's willing to show Kid how his \Ntricks are done before the show starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.65,0:05:38.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And what do you find so amusing, \NKid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.17,0:05:41.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.68,0:05:43.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A-Aoko?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.20,0:05:45.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's with that uniform?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.34,0:05:47.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I told a member of the riot squad
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.00,0:05:50.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,that I wanted to try on the uniform \Nsometime, and he lent me a spare!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.81,0:05:52.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't tell my dad, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.05,0:05:55.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I actually wanted to show him, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.66,0:05:56.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.63,0:05:57.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.50,0:05:59.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Are you gonna fight the bad guy, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.03,0:06:03.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.85,0:06:06.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'll capture him, then \Npound some sense into him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:09.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Because evil musn't be\N allowed to prosper!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.36,0:06:11.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then you're on the same side \Nas Papa! Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.03,0:06:14.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"Papa"? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.74,0:06:18.95,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm Kenta Connery.\N Papa is Chuck Connery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.24,0:06:23.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's been on the trail of that bad guy,\N Nightmare, for the longest time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.00,0:06:26.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's got an important job with Interpol!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.76,0:06:29.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I apologize for arriving late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.58,0:06:34.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is the additional material on Nightmare \NI was telling you about on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:37.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,B-But I didn't think you'd be coming alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.41,0:06:40.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I have people standing by outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.70,0:06:43.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,We're just here to cooperate \Nwith you, the local police.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.94,0:06:45.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,We don't have the right to make an arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.52,0:06:49.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,At any rate, you speak Japanese very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.23,0:06:51.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My wife is Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.87,0:06:53.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Although she passed away three years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.65,0:06:54.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.48,0:06:58.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,K-Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.74,0:07:00.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Shoot! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.89,0:07:03.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.29,0:07:07.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I slipped out of the home since I knew\N you were coming back to Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.24,0:07:08.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"Home"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.66,0:07:12.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ever since my wife passed, I've had \Nan orphanage take care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.37,0:07:17.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I travel all over the world for work,\N so I can't raise him properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.34,0:07:23.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kenta, you "slipped out"? \NI'm sure they're worried about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.25,0:07:26.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's fine! I said I was gonna \Nstay with you at your hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.60,0:07:29.07,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.07,0:07:31.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't have time to drop him \Noff at the home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.76,0:07:33.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I have to go back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.08,0:07:36.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then shall I take him back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.36,0:07:37.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,She's a quick-change artist now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.57,0:07:38.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Um, who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.92,0:07:40.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My daughter, Aoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.66,0:07:43.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,She sometimes brings me dinner \Nwhen I'm on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.56,0:07:45.82,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then please take care of my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.37,0:07:47.82,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.33,0:07:50.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And I'm leaving Nightmare in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.79,0:07:54.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'll arrest him, along with Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.32,0:07:59.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,We've both been carrying heavy baggage for \Nyears, so it'll be nice to finally set it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.17,0:08:00.51,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It will.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.51,0:08:01.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.56,0:08:06.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,One question. Frankly speaking, \Nwhat's Nightmare like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.52,0:08:07.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.96,0:08:11.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If we're to believe the words \Nof all his arrested partners,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.52,0:08:17.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nightmare is a cunning demon \Nwho gets into a person's mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.49,0:08:19.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,sees through everything, \Nand manipulates them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.53,0:08:21.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.80,0:08:25.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A demon who manipulates people's minds...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.17,0:08:27.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That may be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.04,0:08:32.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Kid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.46,0:08:35.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,How is the escape route I selected for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.12,0:08:37.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Worthy of your reputation, Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.18,0:08:41.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, if you know my name already, \Nthat saves us some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.79,0:08:43.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Next Friday the 13th...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.77,0:08:46.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I'm not teaming up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.05,0:08:48.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh? So this is how you're going to play it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.83,0:08:51.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The rumors were right. You're a lone wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.17,0:08:55.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Or actually, you have one associate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.70,0:08:59.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A loyal old man who sometimes \Nimpersonates you and helps you escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:00.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.62,0:09:03.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Maybe now you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.70,0:09:06.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nothing can escape me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.16,0:09:09.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You are under my constant surveillance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.46,0:09:14.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's right. Even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.83,0:09:17.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nightmare!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.21,0:09:19.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So what's the prey?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.71,0:09:25.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nightmare and Kid are after \Nthese earrings, which have
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.02,0:09:27.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,black opals embedded in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.50,0:09:28.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Dark Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.72,0:09:33.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And the jewel is contained in \Nwhat I developed to stymie Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.22,0:09:35.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My security system!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.22,0:09:38.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,To open the lid of that hard glass case,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.66,0:09:42.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,you'd have to remove \Nthese electrified chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.81,0:09:45.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's simple yet impregnable, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.99,0:09:47.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.64,0:09:49.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And what's the liquid in the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.80,0:09:53.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Water! Black opals' weakness is dryness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.03,0:09:55.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Right, Director Kondo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.90,0:10:01.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh, the director said he can't fight on an \Nempty stomach, so he ducked out for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.00,0:10:05.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The outside length and height are 48 cm.\N The diameter inside is 16 cm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.79,0:10:08.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So what do you think of \Nthis system, Kaito-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.14,0:10:11.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't think it can be stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.01,0:10:13.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You'd have to open the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.01,0:10:14.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.56,0:10:16.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Aoko? You're still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.52,0:10:21.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, he insists on "taking down\N the bad guy with Papa."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.63,0:10:25.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's leave this \Nto your papa and my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.15,0:10:29.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Forget it! I'm gonna fight, too!\N I'm gonna be like Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.41,0:10:31.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:33.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.16,0:10:35.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I-I'm fine. I have my medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.41,0:10:38.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's a painkiller!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.15,0:10:45.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The doctor said I have a \Nbad guy living in my head
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.00,0:10:47.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and I need to have surgery...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.32,0:10:48.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Surgery?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.92,0:10:50.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.68,0:10:52.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Papa said!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.03,0:10:57.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If Nightmare goes away, then he'll be able to \Ndrive off the evil, wild horse in my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.84,0:11:01.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then we'll be able to live \Ntogether forever, he said!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.44,0:11:05.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh, are you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.13,0:11:09.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then why don't we get curry and rice\N at a family restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.37,0:11:13.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you eat some carrots, \Nmaybe the bad horse will quiet down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:14.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.78,0:11:17.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Speaking of horses, did you see him in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.42,0:11:18.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Who do you keep talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.84,0:11:20.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.56,0:11:24.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I got a mail saying to let you know \Nhe'd be coming back today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.09,0:11:27.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He said he's looking forward \Nto seeing you at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.78,0:11:30.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, you don't mean {\i1}him{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.00,0:11:33.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Are we really going there, Young Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.40,0:11:36.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's not only Kid who's showing up tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.72,0:11:41.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but I hear some scoundrel with a \Ndreadful name is also connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.93,0:11:43.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Did you know this, Baaya?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.94,0:11:47.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The symbol of a nightmare is a black horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.24,0:11:49.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes, I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.77,0:11:52.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In chess, the black horse is \Na knight that moves second.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.31,0:11:56.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So if the starting white knight \Ndoesn't stand on the board,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.77,0:11:58.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,the game can't begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.08,0:12:01.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I mean me, Saguru Hakuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.08,0:12:01.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,{\i0\fs16}(P.S.: Hakuba literally means white horse.){\i1}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.45,0:12:06.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Between the front, back, \Nin the main building,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.94,0:12:09.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and on the roof, there are \N472 riot police officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.50,0:12:12.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,On top of that, there are six \Nhelicopters watching from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.76,0:12:14.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.52,0:12:18.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But where'd you get that information?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.24,0:12:19.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Surveillance cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.79,0:12:21.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I intercepted footage from the cameras
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:25.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,in the art museum,\N and was just going over it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.90,0:12:32.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes. You could say I possess the power to \Nsee all the information the police have.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.11,0:12:34.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Normally,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.05,0:12:39.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I guide my partner through the \Nescape route I've pre-selected,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.09,0:12:40.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but perhaps you don't need that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.79,0:12:46.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's right. While I do the stealing, \Nyou can pile up the pillows and take a nap,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.54,0:12:48.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nightmare-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.80,0:12:52.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Inspector! Director Kondo is back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.43,0:12:54.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Good grief. You're late, Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.70,0:12:56.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.30,0:12:58.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So how are things going?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.05,0:13:01.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,We were just about to place \NDark Knight into that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.50,0:13:03.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.94,0:13:09.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Just in case, I want to \Ncheck this one last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.33,0:13:14.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It looks like there's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.82,0:13:18.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now I just put the lid back on,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.17,0:13:21.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and then we attach the high-voltage \Nelectrified chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.08,0:13:23.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Whoops! I bumped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.03,0:13:25.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's my age.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.23,0:13:26.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.58,0:13:29.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All right! After you attach \Nthe chains, hang it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.01,0:13:32.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.67,0:13:37.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now, if I can just keep \NHakaba out of the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.59,0:13:42.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Baaya, why are we taking this street?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.10,0:13:47.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Just before, Inspector Nakamori told me this \Nstreet was the fastest way to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.70,0:13:50.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Baaya, that was Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.11,0:13:56.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He used the inspector's voice to lead us \Nto a busy street in order to slow me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.96,0:13:59.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I was such a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.08,0:14:03.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's okay. He knew the situation wouldn't \Nbe good if I arrived before the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.12,0:14:05.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Young Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.41,0:14:06.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'll run the rest of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.34,0:14:10.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hello, Nakamori here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.69,0:14:12.38,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nakamori, it's Saguru Hakaba.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.38,0:14:13.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-Hakaba-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.94,0:14:15.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Inspector, please tell me \Nwhat the situation is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.88,0:14:19.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Situation? Nothing has happened yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.84,0:14:22.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Isn't this room a little too dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.64,0:14:25.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I just adjusted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.49,0:14:28.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Opals contain around 6-10% water,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.91,0:14:33.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and if they dry out, cracks form, \Nso you have to avoid bright lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.54,0:14:35.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.76,0:14:38.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Certainly, when it's dark like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.51,0:14:41.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,you're practically begging \Nfor the opals to be stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.82,0:14:44.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Inspector, the lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.40,0:14:47.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Calm down! Switch to reserve power!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.36,0:14:56.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-The jewels are gone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.21,0:14:58.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-How can it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.17,0:15:00.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's fine. I'm sure they're still inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.91,0:15:04.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Look. They've slid down the pedestal \Nand are floating on the water...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.72,0:15:06.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,They're floating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.85,0:15:08.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.24,0:15:11.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,An opal's specific gravity \Nis between 2.10 and 2.13.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.21,0:15:13.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's no way they could be\N floating in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.36,0:15:15.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Are you telling me they're fakes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.21,0:15:18.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A-Anyway, I'll examine them, so let's \Nremove the chains and the lid...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.61,0:15:21.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Wait! Don't touch anything \Nuntil I get there...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:23.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.37,0:15:26.13,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.84,0:15:30.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-This {\i1}is{\i0} a fake!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.37,0:15:33.38,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,D-Damn you, Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.80,0:15:37.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Chief Connery! We just received \Nword that Kid stole the jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.05,0:15:41.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No problem. I know Nightmare's pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.40,0:15:43.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,After running off, the two \Nof them will rendezvous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.20,0:15:47.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Everyone, follow my orders and act quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.25,0:15:48.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hunt them both down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.52,0:15:49.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.88,0:15:56.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.56,0:15:58.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Papa was in that car!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.66,0:16:00.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Driver, follow that car!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.90,0:16:01.95,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.26,0:16:05.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's something I have to tell Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.08,0:16:09.89,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Someone from the home found a \Nnice doctor who'll fix my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.89,0:16:12.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So he doesn't have to worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.43,0:16:15.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He can concentrate on fighting the bad guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.25,0:16:17.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Please! Let me just tell him that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.90,0:16:19.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.25,0:16:21.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's no point in investigating now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.53,0:16:24.89,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Before the theft, Kid switched \Nthe jewels with fakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.89,0:16:28.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,tilted the case when the lights were out,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.11,0:16:30.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and made us look like fools
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.27,0:16:32.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,for protecting junk jewelry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.27,0:16:34.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Still, don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.28,0:16:38.82,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Normally, with this much \Nwater inside, if you tilt it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.82,0:16:43.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,it should leave grime from the center of the \Nsurface to the side where the water rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.15,0:16:46.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And yet, there's only grime \Non the edges of this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.54,0:16:49.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In other words, the amount \Nof water was very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.29,0:16:52.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.47,0:16:54.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.64,0:16:56.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A transparent acrylic panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.29,0:16:59.38,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He attached a small stopper to \Nall four of the case's corners,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.38,0:17:03.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,sunk an acrylic panel that would get caught \Non them, keeping the depth of the water low.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.31,0:17:08.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A depth that would make the jewels look like \Nthey were floating after he tilted the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.30,0:17:12.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then the fake jewels the director \Nexamined were actually real...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.96,0:17:15.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Inspector! The director is \Nunconscious in the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.94,0:17:17.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's the director!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.42,0:17:20.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid disguised himself as the director \Nand made off with the jewels!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.11,0:17:22.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't let him out of the art museum!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.93,0:17:26.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's probably already discarded that disguise
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.06,0:17:31.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and flown off somewhere on that \Nwhite wing in the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.74,0:17:34.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Crap! Another miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.72,0:17:45.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That was brilliant, Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.24,0:17:50.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh? I thought we were splitting it 50-50.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.19,0:17:53.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, they're not \Nthe jewel I'm looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.26,0:17:58.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What do you think of the escape \Nroute I selected for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.20,0:17:59.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Selected, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.79,0:18:01.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You had tons of choices, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.79,0:18:05.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Because you heard all of the Japanese \Npolice security measures directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.57,0:18:06.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.65,0:18:11.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Jack Connery of Interpol?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:13.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Idiot. I told you already...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.29,0:18:15.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I learned of all the security measures
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.70,0:18:17.91,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,from tapping into cameras \Nand the police network...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.91,0:18:20.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If that's true, why did you \Nmake a counting error?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.34,0:18:21.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Counting?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.42,0:18:24.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Of the riot police: \N136 in front, 103 in back,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.19,0:18:28.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,185 in the main building, 47 on the roof, \Nfor a total of 471 officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.10,0:18:29.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You were one over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.40,0:18:35.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's right. Because you included the \Ngirl who put on the uniform as a lark.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.97,0:18:38.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You didn't intercept the \Nsurveillance cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.69,0:18:41.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You counted with your own eyes \Nright there on the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.29,0:18:46.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I come across them occasionally \Nwhile traveling all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:48.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Stupid local cops
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.90,0:18:54.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,who purposely misreport their numbers to \NInterpol out of pride or burning with rivalry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.53,0:18:58.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's why I always confirm \Nthe numbers with my own eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.45,0:19:00.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but it seems that backfired\N on me this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.46,0:19:01.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.12,0:19:02.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.71,0:19:07.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Any partners who figured out your real \Nidentity were rubbed out by you yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.00,0:19:11.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But my partners are always thieves, \Na plague on their respective countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.61,0:19:17.13,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I give credit to the local cops, ensuring \Nthere's no mention of {\i1}my{\i0} gun being fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.81,0:19:19.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.10,0:19:23.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It seems my people blindly followed my orders\N and brought your local police here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.81,0:19:25.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,To find your corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.81,0:19:30.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You want to help your son so badly\N that you would kill for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.61,0:19:34.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Your son has a complicated cranial disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.57,0:19:36.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You need money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.32,0:19:40.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,When you told him "If Nightmare \Ndisappears, so will your disease,"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.54,0:19:44.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,you meant you would retire as Nightmare\N once you saved up enough for the surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.63,0:19:47.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It must be frustrating to have \Nto give up half every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.46,0:19:52.13,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And yet, if you kept all the treasure for yourself,\N no one would team up with you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.13,0:19:53.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.65,0:19:57.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's why I have to continue \Ngiving nightmares to thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.89,0:20:00.14,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Wearing this mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.14,0:20:03.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.39,0:20:04.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,K-Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.57,0:20:13.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That was Papa! I heard Papa's voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.57,0:20:15.95,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What are you two doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.95,0:20:18.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He said he saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.02,0:20:19.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kenta-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.30,0:20:21.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Let them go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.49,0:20:25.71,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Let the jewels go and grab \Nmy arm with both hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:28.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I can't! This is Kenta's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.64,0:20:30.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kenta's surgery!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.44,0:20:38.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.35,0:20:42.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna be like Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.36,0:20:51.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.68,0:20:55.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ken...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.30,0:21:20.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.76,0:21:23.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He fell trying to protect the jewels?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.40,0:21:26.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Given that he's holding Kid's glove,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.19,0:21:29.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,it looks like Kid was trying \Nto save him from falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.65,0:21:33.71,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The two of them had a falling out \Nand escaped, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.71,0:21:35.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Throwing the treasure aside...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.94,0:21:38.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No. He stole it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.22,0:21:41.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,For his son's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.46,0:21:44.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's the nightmare called truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.36,0:21:54.90,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A sad man who lost his life for \Nthe sake of his beloved son.
